<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,871,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1016,1040]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[321,548,1016,1040]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Bocardiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ligerica">
<emphasis box="[321,548,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Bocardiella ligerica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and specimens from Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[886,971,1015,1039]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Mexico</collectingCountry>
differ in the presence of first notopodial lobes, shape of notochaetae of chaetiger 
<number box="[610,624,1052,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" value="5.0">5</number>
and shape of neurochaetae of chaetigers 
<number box="[1090,1104,1052,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" value="2.0">2</number>
–4, 6, also in presence of low ridges from chaetiger 
<number box="[402,419,1089,1112]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" value="7.0">7</number>
. The identity of specimens from the Grand Caribbean is questionable and should be confirmed against the 
<typeStatus box="[360,408,1125,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
material.
</paragraph>
